The paper introduces new inconsistency measures for pairwise comparisons matrices, which are commonly used in decision-making and ranking problems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.MS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and statistical learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the Monte Carlo simulation, which is a common tool in simulation and modeling research (cs.SI).
